{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f2606094-1af9-4db6-a83d-1889ff2371ed","content":"With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is actually the **default** runner. You only need one change:\n\n### In your project file (`.csproj`):\n\n**Remove** (or set to `false`):\n```xml\n<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n```\n\nThat's it. MSTest.Sdk 3.4+ defaults to Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `UseVSTest` is not set.\n\n### Key differences to be aware of:\n\n| Area | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|------|--------|----------------------------|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (same command) |\n| `.runsettings` | Fully supported | Supported, but some adapters differ |\n| `--filter` | VSTest filter syntax | Same syntax works |\n| CLI options | `--logger`, `--blame`, etc. | Use `--` to pass platform options (e.g., `dotnet test -- --help`) |\n\n### If you use `.runsettings` or custom extensions:\n\n- Review any VSTest-specific logger/adapter configurations — some may need platform-specific equivalents.\n- TRX logging: add `<OutputType>trx</OutputType>` in the project or pass `-- --report-trx` on the CLI.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b1552b54-c964-4dc8-a0e1-813ea4be8280","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in an MSTest project that uses MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nWith MSTest.Sdk, the switch is straightforward:\n\n1. Remove `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` from the project file (or set it to `false`). Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default runner in MSTest.Sdk 3.4+.\n2. That's essentially it for the basic switch.\n\nHowever, there are some additional considerations:\n\n\n- The CLI experience changes: you use `dotnet test` but the underlying runner is different\n- Some VSTest-specific settings/runsettings may need adjustment\n- Extensions and adapters may differ\n\nLet me check if there's anything in the repository that might have more specific guidance.","outputTokens":538,"requestId":"BD08:2F6EDC:1E981EA:2247E1F:6A07C4FA"},"id":"ce9c00cf-655f-4db9-9915-880a017f4fd1","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:14:46.803Z","parentId":"7e64d910-211a-4c99-a4c6-93692339801e"}
